mg src=''http://webdevstudios.com/wp-includes/images/smilies/icon_smile.gif'' alt='':)'' class=''wp-smiley'' />  But right now we want to welcome the awesome <a href="http://webdevstudios.com/team/ryan-duff/">Ryan Duff</a>!</p>\n<p><img class="alignleft size-medium wp-image-6806" title="8177718926_959c9d6866_b" src="http://webdevstudios.com/wp-content/uploads/2012/12/8177718926_959c9d6866_b-300x300.jpg" alt="" width="300" height="300" />Ryan has had an interest in computers since his family got their first computer in 1996. He went from building websites in pure HTML in the late 90′s (blinking text included!) to learning PHP and eventually settling on WordPress in 2004. Wait, 2004 you say? Yes. He’s been using and developing for WordPress for over 8 years. One of Ryan’s earlier contributions to the WordPress community is the no longer maintained WP Contact Form. After consulting on and off over the years, Ryan formed Fusionized Technology and officially got into full time WordPress consulting in 2011. His experience with WordPress has allowed him to get a wide range of clients from individuals to Fortune 500 companies.</p>\n<p>Ryan joins us as the newest addition to our development team. His advanced coding knowledge and coding skills will go to working with some of our biggest clients on their complicated, high traffic websites. We can&#8217;t wait to put him to work (and we are REALLY looking forward to all that tasty BBQ)!</p>\n<p>Read more about Ryan Duff on his <a href="http://webdevstudios.com/team/ryan-duff/">Team Page</a>!</p>\n<div></div>\n";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:36:"http://wellformedweb.org/CommentAPI/";a:1:{s:10:"commentRss";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:77:"http://webdevstudios.com/2012/12/10/were-not-done-yet-welcome-ryan-duff/feed/";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:38:"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/slash/";a:1:{s:8