dios.com/wp-content/uploads/2012/09/show-wplatenight.jpeg" alt="" width="280" height="160" /></a><a href="http://wpcandy.com/category/broadcasts/wp-late-night">WP Late Night</a> is one of the newest WordPress podcasts hosted by <a href="https://twitter.com/dremeda">Dre Armeda</a>, <a href="https://twitter.com/ryanimel">Ryan Imel</a> and WebDevStudios&#8217; <a href="https://twitter.com/williamsba">Brad Williams</a>. Each week the guys sit down (sometime with a special guest!) and discuss current events in the WordPress world such as WordPress updates, new products, WordCamps, and more.</p>\n<p>WP Late Night is certainly not your average tech podcast. The hosts say that WP Late Night is <em>the closest you can get to a WordCamp after party, in handy podcast form </em>and this is no exaggeration. Along with normal WordPress chat there are plenty of beers, sound effects, costume changes and all around tomfoolery.</p>\n<p>Get in on the WP Late Night action by joining in the <a href="http://wpcandy.com/stream">live interactive chat</a>. Find out about upcoming episodes on <a href="http://www.facebook.com/WpLateNight">Facebook</a> or at <a href="http://wplatenight.com">WPLateNight.com</a> and listen in live on the <a href="http://wpcandy.com/stream">WP Candy livestream</a>.</p>\n<p><span style="line-height: 24px;">Missed out on the live recording? Tune in to the latest episode (or any past episode) on </span><a style="line-height: 24px;" href="http://www.youtube.com/user/wpcandydotcom/videos?view=0">YouTube</a><span style="line-height: 24px;">, </span><a style="line-height: 24px;" href="http://itunes.apple.com/us/podcast/wp-late-night/id496147707">iTunes</a><span style="line-height: 24px;">, or download the </span><a style="line-height: 24px;" href="http://wpcandy.com/category/broadcasts/wp-late-night">MP3 file</a><span style="line-height: 24px;">.</span></p>\n<h3><strong>WP Late Night airs live every Wednesday at 8pm Eastern. <a href="http://wpcandy.com/stream">Tune in tonight!</a></strong></h3>\n";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:36:"http://wellformedweb.org/CommentAPI/";a:1:{s:10:"commentRss";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:75:"http://webdevstudios.com/2012/09/26/have-you-tuned-into-wp-late-night/feed/";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:38:"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/slash/";a:1:{s:8:"comments";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:1:"0";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}}}i:7;a:6:{s:4:"data";s:44:"\n		\n		\n		\n		\n		\n				\n		\n\n		\n		\n			\n			\n		\n		";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";s:5:"child";a:5:{s:0:"";a:7:{s:5:"title";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:40:"WordCamp Grand Rapids is just days away!";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:4:"link";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:76:"http://webdevstudios.com/2012/08/16/wordcamp-grand-rapids-is-just-days-away/";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:8:"comments";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:85:"http://webdevstudios.com/2012/08/16/wordcamp-grand-rapids-is-just-days-away/#comments";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:7:"pubDate";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:31:"Thu, 16 Aug 2012 20:24:11 +0000";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:8:"category";a:2:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:8:"WordCamp";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}i:1;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:12:"Grand Rapids";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:4:"guid";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:32:"http://webdevstudios.com/?p=6725";s:7:"attribs";a:1:{s:0:"";a:1:{s:11:"isPermaLink";s:5:"false";}}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:11:"description";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:322:"WordCamp is coming to Grand Rapids, MI this weekend! In just 2 days, Grand Valley State University will be overrun with WordPress enthusiasts spreading lots of WordPress love.  <a href="http://webdevstudios.com/2012/08/16/wordcamp-grand-rapids-is-just-days-away/">Continue reading <span class="meta-nav">&#8594;</span></a>";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:32:"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/";a:1:{s:7:"creator";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:12:"April Heline";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:40:"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/";a:1:{s:7:"encoded";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:2216:"<p><a href="http://2012.grandrapids.wordcamp.org/"><img class="alignleft size-full wp-image-6714" title="WCGR12-WebBanners-Sponsor" src="http://webdevstudios.com/wp-content/uploads/2012/08/WCGR12-WebBanners-Sponsor.png" alt="" width="150" height="150" /></a>WordCamp is coming to Grand Rapids, MI this weekend! In just 2 days, Grand Valley State University will be overrun with WordPress enthusiasts spreading lots of WordPress love.</p>\n<p>The Grand Rapids organizers have worked hard to provide everyone with a jam-packed two days of WordPress goodness.</p>\n<p>Saturday, there will be <a href="http://2012.grandrapids.wordcamp.org/schedule/">4 tracks</a> full of awesome <a href="http://2012.grandrapids.wordcamp.org/speakers/">speakers</a> that want to share their WordPress knowledge and expertise with you.  The Saturday conference will be followed by an afterparty at the <a href="http://2012.grandrapids.wordcamp.org/2012/08/15/party-up/" target="_blank">SpeakEZ Lounge</a>.</p>\n<p>Sunday is <a href="http://2012.grandrapids.wordcamp.org/2012/08/16/what-is-wordpress-study-hall/">WordPress Study Hall</a> where the Grand Rapids organizers are combining the  traditional “Dev Day” that follows most WordCamp events with more user- and attendee-focused opportunities.</p>\n<p>Haven&#8217;t got a ticket yet? Don&#8217;t worry because <a href="http://2012.grandrapids.wordcamp.org/attend/">75 additional tickets</a> were released yesterday and there are plenty still up for grabs! Grand Rapids a little to far for you to travel? You can <a href="http://2012.grandrapids.wordcamp.org/2012/08/14/cant-make-it-but-still-want-to-join-in-the-fun/">tune in</a> remotely via a developer track livestream.</p>\n<p>For more information on WordCamp Grand Rapids, check out the <a href="http://2012.grandrapids.wordcamp.org/">website</a> or follow them on <a href="https://twitter.com/wcgrandrapids/">Twitter</a>.</p>\n<p>Last, we want to give a shout out to our newest WDS team member, <a href="http://webdevstudios.com/team/brian-richards/">Brian Richards</a>, and the organizers who have done so much hard work and planning to bring WordCamp to Western Michigan. We know it&#8217;s going to be a great event!</p>\n";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:36:"http://wellformedweb.org/CommentAPI/";a:1:{s:10:"commentRss";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:81:"http://webdevstudios.com/2012/08/16/wordcamp-grand-rapids-is-just-days-away/feed/";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:38:"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/slash/";a:1:{s:8:"comments";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:1:"0";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}}}i:8;a:6:{s:4:"data";s:47:"\n		\n		\n		\n		\n		\n				\n		\n		\n\n		\n		\n			\n			\n		\n		";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";s:5:"child";a:5:{s:0:"";a:7:{s:5:"title";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:49:"Using WordPress to Help Find the Best of the Best";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:4:"link";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:86:"http://webdevstudios.com/2012/08/09/using-wordpress-to-help-find-the-best-of-the-best/";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:8:"comments";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:95:"http://webdevstudios.com/2012/08/09/using-wordpress-to-help-find-the-best-of-the-best/#comments";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:7:"pubDate";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:31:"Thu, 09 Aug 2012 19:12:46 +0000";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:8:"category";a:3:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:15:"Client Websites";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}i:1;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:9:"WordPress";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}i:2;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:13:"WebDevStudios";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:4:"guid";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:32:"http://webdevstudios.com/?p=6709";s:7:"attribs";a:1:{s:0:"";a:1:{s:11:"isPermaLink";s:5:"false";}}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:11:"description";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:408:"In the past week we have been hard at work launching the Best Of sections for the websites of Philadelphia Magazine and Boston Magazine. Together with magazine publishers, MetroCorp Inc., we worked to create an online directory of their popular &#8230; <a href="http://webdevstudios.com/2012/08/09/using-wordpress-to-help-find-the-best-of-the-best/">Continue reading <span class="meta-nav">&#8594;</span></a>";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:32:"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/";a:1:{s:7:"creator";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:12:"April Heline";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:40:"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/";a:1:{s:7:"encoded";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:2053:"<p>In the past week we have been hard at work launching the Best Of sections for the websites of <a href="http://www.phillymag.com/philly/best-of/" target="_blank">Philadelphia Magazine</a> and <a href="http://www.bostonmagazine.com/boston/best-of/" target="_blank">Boston Magazine</a>. Together with magazine publishers, MetroCorp Inc., we worked to create an online directory of their popular Best Of series for Philadelphia Magazine and Boston Magazine, powered by <a title="WordPress Custom Development and Design" href="http://webdevstudios.com/wordpress/">WordPress</a> of course!</p>\n<p><a href="http://webdevstudios.com/wp-content/uploads/2012/08/Best-of-Philly-2012.png" rel="shadowbox[sbpost-6709];player=img;"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-6702" title="Best of Philly 2012" src="http://webdevstudios.com/wp-content/uploads/2012/08/Best-of-Philly-2012.png" alt="" width="1301" height="1289" /></a></p>\n<p>The Best Of series highlights the most popular and highest rated restaurants, businesses, entertainment and services in the area. Each year these two magazines dedicate one issue to Best Of  highlighting the best of the best in the city and surrounding suburbs. The team wanted to create a clean and organized way to search this list on their website and an easy way to add the winners each year.</p>\n<p><a href="http://webdevstudios.com/wp-content/uploads/2012/08/Best-of-Boston-2012.png" rel="shadowbox[sbpost-6709];player=img;"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-6705" title="Best of Boston 2012" src="http://webdevstudios.com/wp-content/uploads/2012/08/Best-of-Boston-2012.png" alt="" width="1301" height="1465" /></a></p>\n<p>The new Best Of section allows the visitor to scroll through a list of categories and view some information including details about the winner, photos from the location, addresses, phone numbers and website.  Powered by a combination of custom post types, custom taxonomies, and WDS magic, the new Best Of sections make finding the Best of the Best that much easier with WordPress!</p>\n";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:36:"http://wellformedweb.org/CommentAPI/";a:1:{s:10:"commentRss";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:91:"http://webdevstudios.com/2012/08/09/using-wordpress-to-help-find-the-best-of-the-best/feed/";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:38:"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/slash/";a:1:{s:8:"comments";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:1:"0";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}}}i:9;a:6:{s:4:"data";s:50:"\n		\n		\n		\n		\n		\n				\n		\n		\n		\n\n		\n		\n			\n			\n		\n		";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";s:5:"child";a:5:{s:0:"";a:7:{s:5:"title";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:20:"Meet Brian Richards!";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:4:"link";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:56:"http://webdevstudios.com/2012/07/27/meet-brian-richards/";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:8:"comments";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:65:"http://webdevstudios.com/2012/07/27/meet-brian-richards/#comments";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:7:"pubDate";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:31:"Fri, 27 Jul 2012 19:00:43 +0000";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:8:"category";a:4:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:7:"General";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}i:1;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:4:"Team";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}i:2;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:14:"Brian Richards";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}i:3;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:13:"WebDevStudios";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:4:"guid";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:32:"http://webdevstudios.com/?p=6695";s:7:"attribs";a:1:{s:0:"";a:1:{s:11:"isPermaLink";s:5:"false";}}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:11:"description";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:349:"You may have already heard from WP Candy, but WebDevStudios would like to formally welcome you all to meet our newest member, Brian Richards! Brian join us as our newest developer and we are very excited to put him to work! <a href="http://webdevstudios.com/2012/07/27/meet-brian-richards/">Continue reading <span class="meta-nav">&#8594;</span></a>";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:32:"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/";a:1:{s:7:"creator";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:12:"April Heline";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:40:"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/";a:1:{s:7:"encoded";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:1575:"<p>You may have already heard from <a title="brian-richards-joins-the-webdevstudios-team" href="http://wpcandy.com/reports/brian-richards-joins-the-webdevstudios-team">WP Candy</a>, but WebDevStudios would like to formally welcome you all to meet our newest member, Brian Richards! Brian is the newest addition to our development and we are very excited to put him to work!</p>\n<p><img class="alignleft size-medium wp-image-6689" title="me_br" src="https://webdevstudios.com/wp-content/uploads/2012/07/me_br-300x300.jpg" alt="" width="300" height="300" />A little about Brian:</p>\n<p>Brian Richards is the designer-turned-developer behind the the <a href="http://wpstartbox.com/" target="_blank">StartBox</a> theme framework. He spends 80% of all waking hours at a keyboard either creating or solving problems. He has been using WordPress since December 2007 (version 2.3) and has had a hand in launching over 100 WP-powered sites before hanging up his freelance career in 2011.</p>\n<p>Brian graduated with a BS in Photography from Grand Valley State University in 2008, which he claims has been tremendously helpful when coding in PHP because they both begin with &#8220;ph.&#8221; Brian is also the current ranking most remote employee at WDS, hailing from beautiful West Michigan. He&#8217;s a co-organizer for both the <a href="http://meetup.com/wpgrandrapids" target="_blank">WPGR</a> monthly meetups and <a href="http://2012.grandrapids.wordcamp.org/" target="_blank">WordCamp Grand Rapids 2012</a>.</p>\n<p>Welcome Brian! We are happy to have you on the team!</p>\n";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:36:"http://wellformedweb.org/CommentAPI/";a:1:{s:10:"commentRss";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:61:"http://webdevstudios.com/2012/07/27/meet-brian-richards/feed/";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:38:"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/slash/";a:1:{s:8:"comments";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:1:"1";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}}}}}s:44:"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/syndication/";a:2:{s:12:"updatePeriod";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:6:"hourly";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:15:"updateFrequency";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:1:"1";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:27:"http://www.w3.org/2005/Atom";a:1:{s:4:"link";a:2:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:0:"";s:7:"attribs";a:1:{s:0:"";a:3:{s:3:"rel";s:4:"self";s:4:"type";s:19:"application/rss+xml";s:4